  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age from 40 to 60 years.

          2. POP Q stage III &amp; IV

          3. Uterovaginal prolapse.

          4. Vaginal vault prolapse.

          5. BMI &gt;35.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Age &gt; 40 years or &lt; 60 years.

          2. POP Q stage I or II.

          3. BMI &lt; 35.

          4. Previous repair of uterovaginal or vaginal vault prolapse.

          5. Comorbidity with Stress Urinary Incontinence.

          6. Presence of persistent risk factor increasing intra-abdominal pressure e.g. chronic
             chest conditions.

          7. Any significant comorbidity or psychiatric disorder that would compromise patient's
             consent.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
